@sudden6 

> the point is, the clients shouldn't have to care about the concrete algorithm to calculate the checksum. What if it changes one day?

Would it matter? As far as I see it such a change would break things either way.

@SkyzohKey

> It would be useful for ie. copying entire ToxID by custom packets, we could just request the contact nospam and compute the checksum to verify that the received value is correct.

This doesn't make sense to me. The checksum in a Tox ID is only useful to catch errors (such as typos) during the exchange of the public key. It is not needed/useful for the feature you're describing.

@Impyy 

> Would it matter? As far as I see it such a change would break things either way.

It's more about having this be the same among ALL clients. Every client will need such a function, so why not include it in the core?
